UPDATE Single Record
The following SQL updates the record with CustomerID = 1, changing both ContactName and City.

Example:
UPDATE Customers
SET ContactName = 'Alfred Schmidt', City = 'Frankfurt'
WHERE CustomerID = 1;

What this does:
This query changes the ContactName and City fields for the row where CustomerID equals 1.
It updates only that single record because the WHERE clause matches one row.

