UPDATE Multiple Records
The WHERE clause determines which records will be updated.
The following SQL updates ContactName to 'Juan' for all rows where Country is 'Mexico'.

Example:
UPDATE Customers
SET ContactName = 'Juan'
WHERE Country = 'Mexico';

What this does:
This query updates every row where Country is Mexico.
Any matching row receives the new ContactName value.

